## This commit (stage 9/10: completions/image/agent spans — NEW PR this round)
Mirrors the CH completions path:
- _prepare_completion_request imports CompletionPrepResult and
  _setup_completion_model_info from clickhouse_trace_server_batched —
  backend-agnostic business logic that happens to live in the CH module;
  imported rather than forked.
- completions_create: lite_llm_completion, then build_completion_span ->
  _insert_agent_span (dict keyed by span_id = ReplacingMergeTree
  replace); res carries weave_call_id == span_id, trace_id,
  conversation_id (CH parity asserted by
  tests/integrations/litellm/client_completions_create_test.py via
  agent_spans_query read-after-write).
- completions_create_stream: when tracking, writes an OPEN span first
  (ended_at=SENTINEL_EPOCH, UNSET status), yields a _meta first chunk
  with ids, accumulates chunks, and in a finally block replaces the span
  with the completed aggregation (_aggregate_stream_chunks builds the
  chat.completion shape; stream errors recorded on the span and
  re-raised).
- image_create: OPENAI_API_KEY via _secret_fetcher_context,
  lite_llm_image_generation(trace_server=self), then a call_start/
  call_end pair (op weave.image_generation_create, usage keyed by model,
  weave_call_id = call id) — image generation persists a CALL, not a
  span, exactly like CH.
- agent_spans_query: minimal project-scoped query (newest first,
  offset/limit, AgentSpanSchema field intersection, total_count). The
  full AgentQueryHandler surface (stats/search/chat) remains CH-only;
  those tests use CH-only fixtures and skip on the fake.
- _model_to_provider_info_map is a module-level lru_cache(1) function,
  NOT an __init__ attribute, so this dependency lands in this PR (the
  first-use rule) instead of stage 1. CH loads it per-instance in
  __init__; the data is a static file, so sharing the cache is safe.

